body_html:
@vrv. I don't think it is related. The files in tools/dist_test is not depended on by the failing tests.

Looking closer at the log, I noticed that most of failures have the following error:

TypeError: norm() got an unexpected keyword argument 'keepdims'

as well as:

TypeError: linspace() got an unexpected keyword argument 'dtype'

These seem to be some sort of numpy version inconsistency in the functions np.linalg.norm and np.linspace on that particular Mac machine (mac0)

body:
@vrv. I don't think it is related. The files in tools/dist_test is not depended on by the failing tests. 

Looking closer at the log, I noticed that most of failures have the following error: 
```
TypeError: norm() got an unexpected keyword argument 'keepdims'
```

as well as:
```
TypeError: linspace() got an unexpected keyword argument 'dtype'
```

These seem to be some sort of numpy version inconsistency in the functions `np.linalg.norm` and `np.linspace` on that particular Mac machine (mac0)
